{
  "stem": "1537.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And Hungary permitted the Polish army to go through.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Eventually, I think they end up in England, I think, or in Russia, I think.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, just army-- we didn't know about the Jews, nothing, just because they were all in military.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- we didn't know even that the Polish Jew-- when they took us to the ghetto, we didn't even know that the Polish Jew was liquidated-- three and a half million Jews.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The only thing I remember, you know, was getting-- you know, we are jumping back and forth through the story.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every time when I used to study in [INAUDIBLE], the seven kilometers-- the seven miles-- from Somotor, the rabbi used to ask me all these questions.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because I was always interested in politics, even as a kid.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Every time they were talking in shul after davening, after praying, they said, Roosevelt.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Roosevelt, Churchill will save us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in my mind-- you know, I didn't know how serious it is.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In my mind, I was sure Roosevelt, President Roosevelt and Churchill will save, save us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It never happened.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Unfortunately, I had to come here to find out that President Roosevelt was an anti-Semite.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But this is another story for another day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Tell me about your bar mitzvah, 1941.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'41 or '42, something like this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My bar mitzvah was in [INAUDIBLE] because then-- because I used to come home once a year only.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because it was hard already.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, you had to feed another person.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they needed me in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I had to go to cheder, to yeshiva, in the morning, 5 o'clock in the morning till 7:00, yeshiva. 7:00, go to shul, you go round to my uncle to eat breakfast. 8 o'clock, we are to go to school.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
